The sketch above has already provided plenty of reasons why this system
 might be interesting to examine, and there is a variety of literature that
 looks into it, usually from the standpoint of a measure-peserving chaotic
 dynamical system.
 I won't provide a literature review here, other than to say all of the
 usual phenomena associated with iterated chaotic systems appears here as
 well.
 The goal of this text is not to repeat old news, but to focus on new things.
 Yet, some repetition of the well-known is unavoidable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This text was originally inspired by the topology of the Moore plane.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
See Wikipedia, 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
