\begin_layout Standard
Informally, the measure can be understood as a single slice through the
 Feigenbaum map.
 In the periodic regions, it will be of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\left(x\right)=\sum_{k}\delta\left(x-x_{k}\right)$
\end_inset

 where the sum ranges over the points 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{k}$
\end_inset

 in the cycle, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

